<br>
Ya might know me from such hairbrained schemes as the red named newbie crew that was running around for a few weeks.  Well, alot of us are lookin to move to Test.<br>
<br>
I want to stay here.  I really like it here, and a few others do too.  I haven't experienced all there is to see in Everquest, and neither has a friend of mine.  I was a lvl 40 druid and 45 warrior on Tallon Zek with over 150 days /played combined (never sought leveling, it just sorta happened), and I haven't played in two years so I'm a super noob.))<br>
<br>
Anywho, there are a few of us who want to start over here and try to catch up with the big folks.  Right now we have a human monk, a halfling warrior and I'm thinkin of becomin a halfling rogue.  I think we're pretty good folk to be around, we just like to have fun, but we want to get strong pretty fast (I can't stand levelin), and once we hit 50 we'll slow down a bit.<br>
<br>
Basically what I'm askin is if any of ya know anyone who is startin over and needs some huntin companions.  We're gonna be goin pretty fast and focused on gettin stronger and not gettin richer (read- exp &gt; equipment).  We'd really like some kinda healer, but any nice folk who might like to group with us would be nice.  We're probably stayin in the old world (Antonica/Kunark/Velious) until we hit the 50 mark, so keep that in mind.<br>
<br>
Give me a tell sometime or reply so I can look for ya.  If ya don't mind me talkin yer ear off,that is.<br>
<br>
Oh and thanks everyone who has made Fironia Vie an amazing server in the few weeks that I have been here.  Hope everyone is like the folks I meet... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=generalstarkweather>General Starkweather</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/9/03 2:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm42.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=313.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Blood</span><hr size=1> Each to his own ofcourse, but I would advice you to stop and smell the flowers, and enjoy the view on the way up. There is alot of opportunity for excellent adventure and roleplaying encounters in all the levels.<br>
Another piece of advice I give is that if you plan on mingling in with all the roleplayers on FV, it is a good idea to take a brief moment to flesh out the basics of your character, and especially what side he or she supports, if any, in this whole eternal Good vs Evil struggle.<br>
<br>
Have fun and I am sure you will enjoy your time on FV, as this is the best server, with the kindest people of all the available servers. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">General <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Stoppelton Starkweather</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
<!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=695966" target="top">Magelo profile</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xaruul>Xaruul</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/9/03 5:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm42.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=313.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Blood</span><hr size=1> ooc - Rereading my post, it sounds a bit powergamish.  I couldn't be less of a powergamer than I am.  I am a pretty big roleplayer, and try to stay in character as much as possible.  The reason I want to get strong fast is two fold - one is because I lose interest fast if I am try to level and getting nowhere, especially if there is no one around at the younger levels.  Two is because I have already experienced the lower levels and just about all they have to offer in my past TZ days.  Like I said, 150 days played with two characters under 45, I pretty much did every quest and went to every zone I could, evil and good.<br>
<br>
As far as roleplaying and stories...I usually prefer to let them happen.  Me and my friend Fuff, we bring a personality to a character and then just...go.  Most of the stories I have are after the fact (I love big adventure posts with screenshots and stories...dialups beware).  I rarely have anything planned, cause I think it's more fun to improvise and just go with the flow.  I was thinkin about havin a group of folks with a storyline already fleshed out, but my friends already have their characters picked out that don't work with the thoughts I've had.  So we'll just wing it.<br>
<br>
(I wanted to be an ogre warrior who has a life debt to a gnome or halfie cleric.  The cleric doesn't really like the ogre, he's a dummy, but he is helpful in a pinch and always sacrifices himself for the cleric.  The cleric is usually short with him but the ogre is clueless.  This would be somewhat of a samurai situation, where the ogre feels like he owes the cleric his life (the cleric saved his when he was young, not quite sure how yet).  Anyway, that is one thing I wanted to do, but no one i know wants to play a cleric, and it would be a tough time findin a guild that would accept both a gnome and an ogre, I think).<br>
<br>
So, in conclusion, I'm a nut and your better off talkin to me in game.  Beewindy's the name.  (hey that rhymes) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=beewindy>Beewindy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/9/03 5:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm42.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=313.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Blood</span><hr size=1> Dangit I always do that.  Xaruul is the lizzie warrior I was in a previous life.  Bee's the one you want to talk to.<br>
