<br>
The other night when the server crashed, five of my Legionairres headed over to Stromm, made level one gnomes, and wreacked havoc for about half an hour. In the process, we met a nice little gnome cleric named Janet. She buffed us with her level one spell, then all my people ran off toward the Knowledge book. I was still close enough to Janet to hear her sigh, clearly disappointed. She seemed lonely, so once the server was back up and I had Koko out of danger, I sent a tell to her inviting her to join us on Firiona Vie.<br>
<br>
She's here now, she's a level 5 halfling cleric named Jeanett, give her a shout. She's new to the game completely, but she's very sweet and happy to learn. Idanya spent a while helping her learn to communicate better.<br>
<br>
As much as I like doing the stuff we do at the higher end of the guild, there's nothing I love more than having a true newbie learning the ropes that we can mentor. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.boomspeed.com/kolanifv/crit.JPG" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
